This paper discusses the analysis of logic programs, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the incorporation of explicit structural information, which is related to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper evaluates the precision gains of various domain combinations, which is related to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of tracking compoundness, which is related to the sub-category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
